clinical text in
│
│── stage 1: extraction
│   send text to UMLS API, get back CUIs by embedding similarity
│   params: top_k=6, top_p=5000, combined=true
│   then run medspacy ConText (102 rules, batch_parse)
│   negated phrases → drop their CUIs
│   cache: API results yes, ConText no (same phrase can be negated in one doc, not another)
│
│── stage 2: SAB filter
│   keep SNOMEDCT_US only, drop ICD10/ICD9/everything else
│   one vocab = one hierarchy = no conflicts in stage 4
│
│── stage 3: metadata + IC
│   fetch semantic types from BQ (_BQ_BATCH=5000)
│   IC = -log((desc+1)/total), precomputed for 2.3M nodes, dict lookup
│   higher IC = more specific
│
│── stage 4: hierarchy reduction
│   ancestor_depth = log(20)/log(mean_in_degree), clamped [1,5]
│   SNOMED → 5, ICD10 → 3 (fallback, log(1.0) breaks)
│   computed once from graph, same every run
│   walk UP 1 hop: if parent also in set + IC(child) >= IC(parent) + same type → drop parent
│
│── stage 5: embedding dedup
│   fetch 3072-dim embeddings from BQ
│
│   n <= 20? → fast path (otsu + guards on full matrix)
│   n > 20?  → louvain path:
│     k-NN graph: k=20, edge threshold = mean of k-th neighbor dists (one per CUI, not all pairs)
│     louvain: resolution=1.0, seed=42, groups cuis by modularity, removes nothing
│     then otsu + guards WITHIN each community separately
│
│   otsu: sort pairwise dists, try every split
│     score = w0 * w1 * (m0 - m1)^2, pick highest
│     cap at median so never > 50% flagged
│     below threshold → check guards
│     above → skip
│
│   guards (any fires → keep both, all fail → remove lower IC):
│     g1: parent-child edge (O(1))
│     g2: semantic types disjoint (O(|types|))
│     g3: ancestor sets disjoint (BFS up [1,5])
│     g4: sibling leaves (O(1))
│
│   singletons merged if sim > mean(within-group) * 0.5
│
│   confidence scoring: prox/cent/ret, variance-weighted
│   just ranks the CSV, doesn't affect anything
│
└── out: deduplicated surviving CUIs → topic formation


surviving CUIs in (just codes, no text, no phrases)
│
│── stage 6: hierarchical topic builder
│   IC floor = p10 of surviving CUI ICs (one number, not an average)
│   max_coverage = max(2, n/sqrt(n))
│
│   BFS UP from every CUI:
│     hard cap: 5 hops
│     gradient: at hop 3+, stop if IC(parent) < 0.3 * IC(current)
│     hop 1-2 always walk (grace period)
│     collects everything, floor filters AFTER
│
│   3 rules for an ancestor to become a grouping key:
│     1. covers >= 2 surviving CUIs
│     2. IC >= floor
│     3. not in the surviving set itself
│     all three pass → grouping key
│
│   convergence selection:
│     sort passing ancestors by IC desc, greedy assign
│     highest IC → subtopics
│     ancestor of 2+ subtopics → topic grouper
│     leftovers → singletons
│
│   each topic gets: SNOMED label, topic_cui, member CUIs, subtopics
│
│── stage 7: reps + anchors
│   per topic: split by semantic type, HAC at 0.5, 1 rep per sub-cluster
│   anchors (docs only): BFS up 4 hops from reps, IC_MIN=4.0
│
│── stage 8: centroids
│   mean of member CUI embeddings, L2-normalized, 3072-dim
│
└── out: topics with labels + centroids → query matching
